<p>And then there&rsquo;s the art they like to get, and the basement has a lot of tools and additional storage, and then there&rsquo;s another old fridge in the garage, and the dining room has a table, but you can also eat in the kitchen - but why? I feel like I&rsquo;m criticizing and not coming from the angle of &ldquo;this is wrong,&rdquo; I just don&rsquo;t get it. Maybe if I were to live in a place like this for a while, I would. What do you get out of the extra space and extra stuff?</p>
